<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-27-0660 </DOCNO><TEXT>39 patients, who were irradiated with doses of 50 to 70 Gy for ENT-tumorsover a period of 3.5 months to three years prior to the examination,showed a rapidly progressing caries of the teeth inside the target volume.The teeth outside the target volume developed a caries of less extent.Radiation induced xerostomia, effects of the irradiation of the softtissues, nutrition habits and hygienics are discussed as causes for thedamage of the teeth.</TEXT></DOC>